---
import Accordion from './Accordion.astro';
import SectionLabel from './SectionLabel.astro';

const items = [
  {
    q: 'How is the sprint priced?',
    a: 'Fixed fee, quoted after the free waste audit and tied to your current spend — not hourly. If we don’t hit the agreed savings percentage within 30 days of handoff, you don’t pay. The audit call itself is free and carries no obligation.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Do you need access to our prompts and data?',
    a: 'We work from usage metadata — token counts, cache hit rates, model and endpoint mix, request traces — not your training data or customer content. Where prompt inspection is needed, it happens in your environment under your access controls, and we sign an NDA before the audit.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Which providers do you support?',
    a: 'We’re model-agnostic: Claude (Anthropic), OpenAI, and Gemini, plus open-weight models behind vLLM or Bedrock. The levers — caching, compaction, trimming, guardrails — apply anywhere tokens are billed.',
  },
  {
    q: 'How much engineering effort does this take from our team?',
    a: 'Week 2 is done-for-you: we open the PRs, your team reviews them. Most clients budget a few hours of review per week plus one 30-minute sync. Attribution instrumentation is a thin middleware layer, not a re-architecture.',
  },
  {
    q: 'How does the guarantee actually work?',
    a: 'In week 1 we sign off on a measured baseline and a target savings percentage. Thirty days after handoff, we compare like-for-like usage against that baseline. Hit the target, the fee stands; miss it, you don’t pay. Terms are in the engagement letter — no asterisks.',
  },
];
---

<section id="faq" class="border-t border-rule py-20 sm:py-28">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 sm:px-10">
    <SectionLabel index="07" label="Fair questions" />
    <h2 class="display mt-8 text-[2.25rem] leading-[1.05] sm:text-[3rem]">
      Before you <em class="display-italic">ask</em>.
    </h2>
    <div class="mt-12">
      <Accordion items={items} />
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
